{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"darksome-collusive-reindeer","description":"## What\n\nThe root `README.md` documents the session-log command without its required\nsubcommand, which the CLI rejects — a P0 onboarding defect that directly\ncontradicts `docs/user-guide.md`.\n\n- `README.md:333` shows `rebar session-log \"<entry>\"` (no subcommand).\n- The CLI (`src/rebar/_commands/session_log.py`) consumes the first positional as the\n  verb and errors with `unknown session-log action` for anything but `append`/`start`.\n- `docs/user-guide.md:170-171` already shows the correct `rebar session-log append\n  \"<entry>\"` / `rebar session-log start` forms.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `README.md` shows a valid, copy-pasteable session-log invocation using the\n      `append` subcommand (and mentions `start` for rotation), matching\n      `docs/user-guide.md`.\n- [ ] The command as printed in `README.md` runs without the `unknown session-log\n      action` error.\n- [ ] No other doc still shows the bare `rebar session-log \"<entry>\"` form.\n\nFiles: `README.md` (line ~333).","id":"a41f-3153-9292-4e76","parent_id":"4191-b4f9-146a-43cd","priority":1,"tags":["docs","p0"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"P0: Fix README session-log command syntax (add subcommand)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783814559454271001,"uuid":"3535bea2-4153-4b13-b419-46fa56cf1b26"}